g.aria-label: World loss of life and economic damage, as of 2015, from major types of pollution. Monetary damages are based on willingness to pay to avoid harm and on lost productivity, but do notinclude ecosystem damages. Health damages may furthermore be underestimated, as theyare based only on established pathways from pollution to disease. Source:Landrigan et al..Landrigan, P. et al. "TheLancetCommission on pollution and health". The Lancet Commissions391(10119), pp.462-512.February 2018.
